<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-424-749  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 424 749.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Sept 11 1990 v4 n30 p22(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Paradigm writes new rules for Object Logo. (Object Logo 2.5)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Webster, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Paradigm Software Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Object Logo 2.5 (Program development software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionLOGOObject-Oriented ProgrammingSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By John WebsterandM;Cambridge, Mass.andP;  -- As Apple readies lower-cost machines that shouldincrease the Mac's popularity in the K-12 arena, Paradigm Software Inc. lastmonth introduced a new version of Object Logo, an object-oriented Macimplementation of the popular Logo educational programming environment.andM;Called Object Logo 2.5, the $149 language is derived from a product firstmarketed in 1987 by Coral Software, a Cambridge, Mass.-based languagedeveloper Apple acquired last year.andP;  Apple continues to own the software, butParadigm said a recent agreement gives it complete responsibility for futuredevelopment, marketing and support.andM;&quot;The fact that Apple has renewed the push into the education market with thepromise of low-cost color suggests a large market for Object Logo,&quot; saidHazem Sayed, Paradigm president.andM;Teacher-developers vouch for the educational value of Object Logo, whichincludes a Turtle Object designed to walk students through mathematicalproblems.andP;  &quot;We're teaching Euclidean geometry in the Cartesian plane tostudents at all levels -- elementary, high school, college, even teachers,&quot;said Ronald Genise, a mathematics and computer science instructor who is headof the Unified Math and Computer Science Laboratory at a San Jose, Calif.,andO;middle school.andM;The school developed a tutorial called Rene's Place (for Rene Descartes) that&quot;weds geometry and algebra,&quot; Genise said.andM;New features in Version 2.5, which is designed for university as well aselementary and secondary students, include:andM;andgt;Hierarchical menus integrated with the Mac interface to simplify programwriting and editing.andM;andgt;32-bit color QuickDraw, up from eight bits.andM;andgt;Enhanced list processing, combining artificial intelligence andnatural-language processing for creating applications.andM;andgt;Enhanced mathematics, including geometry and algorithmic formulas.andM;Version 2.5 is available for $55 to current Object Logo users.andM;Paradigm Software Inc. can be reached at P.O. Box 2995, Cambridge, Mass.andO;02238; (617) 576-7680.andO;</TEXT></DOC>